    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — what the Chronicler intends by assembling these six tribal registers at this point in his work, and what the canonical context of each tribe's data contributes to the argument. The movements below follow the chapter's own structure: tribal summaries understood as theology, the Ephraimite narrative as covenant paradigm, and the territorial summary as pastoral land-theology for a displaced community. Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens the meaning, a note follows the main interpretation.",
